        <abstract> 
<p>Comments on David Milne’s paper ["On the parallel roads of Lochaber" (1847), <hi rend="italic">Trans. R. Soc. Edinburgh</hi> 16 (1849): 395–418]. CD still believes in marine origin. Rejects barrier of detritus at mouth of Glen Roy. If roads were formed by lake, it must have been ice-lake.</p> 
            <p>Comments on evidence of glaciers and icebergs in North Wales. Thinks pass caused by tidal channel, not river. Suggests that RC make altitude measurements at various points.</p>
        </abstract>
